title: Grateful Dead Live at McNichols Sports Arena on 1981-07-13
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > R8Brain > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 05/2016
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, They Love Each Other-> El Paso, Jack A Roe-> Beat It On Down The Line, It Must Have Been The Roses-> CC Rider, Althea-> Looks Like Rain-> Deal

Set 2

Women Are Smarter-> Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Estimated Prophet-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Satisfaction

reviews.review_text: Very Sweet relaxed yet inspired show! Pitch correction is on point! This show is best heard with this outstanding audience recording as the band was clearly milking the poor acoustics of McNichols to their advantage; something they were uniquely adept at doing! Check out the thunderous transition into fire with Phil showing us his magic fully!!! Of course the downside with this  recording is part of first set missing. But the upside is that it is the only one pitch corrected. ALL of the soundboards run very fast a full half step fast in terms of pitch. Ugh. Maybe someone will pitch correct those. But frankly this is show needs an audience recording anyway and this one is fantastic!
